    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; JDepend 1.4, the freely-available Java 
    &gt; package dependency
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; analyzer,  has
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; been released.  Of particular interest to 
    &gt; JUnit users is
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; the ability to
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; write tests that automatically check 
    &gt; metrics tolerances,
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; existence of
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; package dependency cycles, and package dependency
    &gt; &gt; &gt; constraints.
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; New Features:
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; - Added package dependency constraints to 
    &gt; support writing
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; tests that
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; fail if any package dependency other than 
    &gt; those declared in
    &gt; &gt; &gt; the
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; dependency constraints are detected.  Refer to the
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; documentation or the
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; jdepend.framework.ConstraintTest class for complete
    &gt; &gt; &gt; examples.
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;   For example, the following test case 
    &gt; method will fail
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; if the analyzed
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; packages contain any dependencies other 
    &gt; than those declared
    &gt; &gt; &gt; in
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; the
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; dependency constraint:
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;     public void testDependencyConstraint() {
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage ejb = new 
    &gt; JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.ejb&quot;);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage web = new 
    &gt; JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.web&quot;);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         JavaPackage util = new 
    &gt; JavaPackage(&quot;com.xyz.util&quot;);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         ejb.dependsUpon(util);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         web.dependsUpon(util);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         DependencyConstraint constraint = new
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; DependencyConstraint();
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(ejb);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(web);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         constraint.addPackage(util);
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         _jdepend.analyze();
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;         
    &gt; assert(_jdepend.dependencyMatch(constraint));
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;     }
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; - Added the jdepend.xmlui.JDepend class to generate
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; package metrics,
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; dependencies, and cycles in an XML format for easier
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; integration with
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt; other tools.
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;   Example usage:
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;       java jdepend.xmlui.JDepend -file report.xml
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; /myproject/src
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
    &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt; &gt;     &gt;
